arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase VI: Late Nabataean pre CE 106 minor collapses and repairs. Probable early collapse of the Baroque Room and damage occurs in both the Anteroom and Shrine Room. The tabun in Room A is used to store CE 1st c. Nabataean fine wares. East 'Cistern" used as a dump. Bath Complex built.
0.93 m north south-by- 0.37 m east west.

The west brick arch is built into the south and north wall as a weight bearing instillation for the floor. The arch along with its east component provided further superstructure buttressing for the pavers over the empty water chamber area. The arch is composed of 18 bricks laid with hydraulic stucco.
In the east middle section of the water chamber.
Construction of the Well Room and the canalization system.
